President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Judge Amul R. Thapar of Kentucky for the U.S. Court of Appeals for the Sixth Circuit. Judge Thapar, the son of Indian-American immigrants, currently serves on the District Court for the Eastern District of Kentucky. If confirmed, he will become the first Article III judge of South Asian descent. Prior to his judicial career, Judge Thapar was the U.S. Attorney for the Eastern District of Kentucky and served as an Assistant U.S. Attorney in the Southern District of Ohio and the District of Columbia. He began his legal career in private practice and holds a BS from Boston College and a JD from the University of California, Berkeley.